    "description": "\nHeavy snow expected.\n\nWhat:\nTotal snowfall accumulations of 10 to 20 cm.\nReduced visibility in heavy snow and local blowing snow.\n\nWhen:\nTonight into Tuesday evening.\n\nAdditional information:\nPrecipitation will begin as rain before changing to snow. There is also a risk of freezing rain during this transition.\n\n###\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@ec.gc.ca or post reports on X using #ONStorm.\n",
